description.narrative:
1)  100 end-users such as builders, architects, banks and different government organizations sensitized on use of REB products.  500 brick kiln entrepreneurs sensitized on the technologies available for REBs;
2)  Detailed Project Report for Bangalore, Punjab/Haryana brick clusters prepared.  Five meetings held with banks and financial institutions at regional/cluster level for familiarizing them on REB technology adoption.  Interest of banks will be visible once they start accepting the loan documents;
3)  REBs sold in the market and used for construction.  Approach paper for developing market for REBs.  Report on fly ash bricks, technology use and barriers for adoption prepared. 
4)  Local Resource Centres established in West, East and North-East regions to initiate cluster-level activities.  List of potential brick kiln entrepreneurs prepared for all five regions.  Technologies identified for all regions.  Two entrepreneurs adopted technologies for REB production.  Technologies for production of REBs documented along with technical specifications and costs. 
5)  At least 5 brick kiln entreprises in each cluster invest in technology upgradation by end of the project.  Exposure visits organized for interested entrepreneurs from different regions.  Project brochure prepared and shared with at least 600 shareholders.  Project website launched and available for sharing knowledge on REBs.

comment.narrative:
1)  Very limited usage of Resource Efficient Bricks (REBs) in construction sector.  80 brick kiln entrepreneurs sensitized on REBs.
2)  No proper document exists to avail loan from the banks for technology upgradation in brick industry;
3)  Knowledge among brick kiln entrepreneurs and market share of REBs is very low;
4)  No REB kiln units existing at present;
5)  Knowledge and capacities of brick kiln entrepreneurs for adopting resource efficient technologies are low.  No information delivery system exists in brick sector.

